TL;DR If you want to cut to the chase, here&rsquo;s the complete list of commands:
# Download the Python 3.6.4 installer with PowerShell Invoke-WebRequest -Uri 'https://www.python.org/ftp/python/3.6.4/python-3.6.4-amd64.exe' -OutFile '.\python-3.6.4-amd64.exe' # Passive Install of Python for All Users # Run this from an elevated PowerShell prompt .\python-3.6.4-amd64.exe /passive TargetDir=&quot;C:\Python&quot; InstallAllUsers=1 PrependPath=1 Include_test=0  Run these in a new PowerShell window after installing Python:
# Install Azure CLI system-wide pip install azure-cli # Upgrade Azure CLI later on pip install --upgrade azure-cli  For a fuller explanation, read on&hellip;
